<p><xref ref="def-limit" /></p>

<p>This definition has a topological version.</p>

<definition xml:id="def-limit-top">
  <title>Functional Limit: Topological Version</title>
  <statement>
    <p>
      Let <m>f:A \rightarrow \mathbb{R}</m> and let <m>c</m> be a limit point of the domain <m>A</m>.  We say that <m>\lim_{x \rightarrow c} f(x)=L</m> provided that, for every <m>\epsilon-</m>neighborhood <m>V_{\epsilon}(L)</m> of <m>L</m> there exists a <m>\delta-</m>neighborhood <m>V_{\delta}(c)</m> of <m>c</m> with the property that for all <m>x \in V_{\delta}(c)</m> different from <m>c</m> (with <m>x \in A</m>) it follows that <m>f(x) \in V_{\epsilon}(L)</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
</definition>

<example>
  <title>Limit of a linear function</title>
  <p workspace="4in">Prove that <m>\displaystyle \lim_{x \rightarrow 1} 3x-7=-4</m>.</p>
  
</example>

</section>

