<section>
<<<<<<< HEAD
  <title>Continuous Functions</title>
  
<p workspace="4in"></p>

<definition xml:id="def-cts">
  <title>Continuity at a point</title>
  
  
  <statement>
    <p>
      A function <m>f:A \rightarrow \mathbb{R}</m> is continuous at a point <m>c \in A</m> if, for all <m>\epsilon &gt; 0</m> there exists a <m>\delta &gt; 0</m> such that whenever <m>|x-c| &lt; \delta</m> (and <m>a \in A</m>) it follows that <m>|f(x)-f(c)| &lt; \epsilon</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
</definition>

<p>Note here that the value of <m>\delta</m> depends on both <m>\epsilon</m> and <m>c</m>, so we write <m>\delta=\delta(\epsilon,c)</m>.</p>

<definition xml:id="def-ctsonA">
  <title>Continuous on a set</title>
  <statement>
    <p>
     If <m>f: A \rightarrow \mathbb{R}</m> is continuous at every point in the domain <m>A</m> we say <m>f</m> is continuous on <m>A</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
</definition>

